1. Problem Statement
Marathon, Bungie’s extraction shooter launching March 5, 2026, features 7 Runner Shell classes, Cores that modify abilities, Implants that boost stats, and over 400 weapon mods. Players who want to maximize their characters face a combinatorial optimization problem that is impossible to solve manually. Without tooling, players will waste resources experimenting with suboptimal builds, lose valuable gear on failed extractions due to poor loadout decisions, and miss weekly objectives that maximize progression.
The Destiny 2 ecosystem proves the demand: DIM has millions of active users, D2ArmorPicker is the most-visited Destiny optimization tool, and Light.gg serves 35M+ users with weapon data. No equivalent tooling exists for Marathon. The first comprehensive companion app to market will capture this audience.
